 &quot; It is good to see you again, Rhiannon.... I had a pleasant ride here. I came to ask about the tribe we spoke about. As you know, certain land issues are what concerns Hippolyte and myself, and I assured her that we can all come to an agreement to where everyone would be at peace with it.<br>
 I know that my reputation as being a fair amazon, has yet to reach you. But my word is solid and true. When I was queen so long ago, I was a fair one. Of course, I was also a little quicker to fight than I am now. I tend to pick those fights that are worthy of being fought.&quot; <br>
 Solari followed her friend back into the Main Hall. She glanced around and smiled softly. <br>
 &quot;The only things I can think we need to discuss are the issues of land and things of that nature. But, Let us get to that later, If you would please humor me, a tour of your villiage. &quot; And with that she smiled softly, but proudly at her friend. ~<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/urhiannonmerai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhiannon Mer ai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#993300>(9/5/02 11:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm55.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.absolutely.net/hannigan/ah26.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~A Visitor~</span><hr size=1> Rhiannon, being the younger and more energetic of the two, beamed. &quot;Of course I'll show you around! Just leave your things here and we'll come back for them later.&quot;<br>
She exited the Main Hall and headed for the outskirts of the village.<br>
Rhia started with the Stables, the tribe's pride and joy. &quot;We breed the finest horses in the Nation. We're currently working out a trade agreement with Chadesia. Metalwork for horseflesh.&quot; Rhiannon seemed delighted by the idea. <br>
<br>
She'd been a bit skeptical at first, with Marpesia being so isolated from most of the rest of the tribes. But with the trade agreement, and with her going back and forth between Marpesia and Hyrcania so much, they were starting to get alot more visitors of late. <p><center> <img src = "http://user.netomia.com/angelkim/rhia.png"><br>
