  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/urhiannonmerai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhiannon Mer ai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen of the Amazon Nation Alliance</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#993300>(9/13/02 10:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm55.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.absolutely.net/hannigan/ah26.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~A Visitor~</span><hr size=1> The Hall was empty at this time, as it was only used for feasts and other special occasions. There was a long wooden table in the center of the room, and benchs placed all along the sides. At each end, there was a single chair, one for each of the Queens. <br>
<br>
The room was longer than it was wide, to accomodate the table and so many people. Along the left wall were extra benches, and along the right wall were some more tables. on the floor along the edges were layed rushes, and herbs, to keep the room from going stale between feasts. <br>
<br>
Rhiannon sat down at the table, on a bench, and motioned for Solari to do likewise.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sit, Sister, you must be tired after the trip up the mountains. We'll rest a moment, and then continue.&quot; <p><center> <img src = "http://user.netomia.com/angelkim/rhia.png"><br>
