<br>
She unrolled it, and revealed a map of the Caucasus Mtns. She pinned the sides down to the table, facing Solari, then began.<br>
<br>
&quot;As you can see, our land covers quite a bit of territory. These mountains are not small by any means.&quot; Rhia smiled softly. &quot;There is plenty of room for two tribes to co-exist and never actually meet. However, there is one small hitch.&quot; She pointed to a small x on the map, located in a valley. &quot;This is where our tribe is, &quot; she moved her finger to the next valley over to the east, to another small x. &quot;and this is where your tribe used to be. They are terribly close together, which makes simply splitting the lands in two more difficult. But i think we can work around that. What I think will need to happen for this to be a viable plan is that we need to make some sort of agreement. For instance, you'll hunt these lands one year, and we'll hunt the land farther out, then the next year we switch. Or something similar to that.&quot; The young woman took a deep breath, surprised at herself for having said so much. &quot;What do you think?&quot; <p><center> <img src = "http://user.netomia.com/angelkim/rhia.png"><br>
