     She was unaware that anyone was in the chamber and walked in as if she owned the world.  And on some days she certain felt she did.  She stopped when she heard Rhia's voice, then another female voice.  She listened for a few minutes and then stepped just inside the main room, arms crossed over her chest.  She had been taught her entirely life that she was to fight for what was hers and her sisters.  Now someone was challenging that and an Amazon at that.  <br>
     She cleared her throat and raised a dark brow, waiting for the other two women's attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/urhiannonmerai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhiannon Mer ai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#993300>(10/5/02 10:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm55.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.absolutely.net/hannigan/ah26.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Returning a Scroll</span><hr size=1> At the sound of a throat being cleared, Rhiannon looked around and saw Doriana standing in the doorway, arms crossed and a beligerent gleam to her eyes. She smiled broadly.<br>
